She has a story that is breathtaking! If you see her around, please give her a big Congrats. This is well deserved.

Scott Bryan
May 15 at 3:55 PM ·

The Gadsden County Times is publishing its annual graduation section in its May 28 edition of the newspaper. If you'd like to congratulate your outstanding student, you can do so with these incredibly affordable rates.

Additionally, I'd be remiss if I didn't offer an immense amount of praise for Tika Wiggins-Milton with Gadsden County Public Schools, Debbie Potter with Robert F. Munroe Day School and Kim Truett with Tallavana Christian School, who ensured The Times had all available senior photos to include in this special keepsake edition. Those three women's work, organization and patience with me is a big reason why we'll be able to publish this great section highlighting the seniors' graduation. Thank you to those three for all you do in our community.

Congrats Class of 2020!

I’m very excited to announce that Keith Bush has committed and signed with Hillsborough Community College. This one brings tears to my eyes. The growth that this young man has demonstrated over this past year not just as a basketball player but as a young man has been remarkable. No one knows your story better than you do And I hope you will get to a point where you are ready to share it with the world. Continue to live life and perform with that same energy and passion that you are known for. Much love and respect! Gadsden County Public Library System
March 31 at 4:44 PM ·

Sign up for a Library Card number to access e-books, audiobooks and other educational classes send sign-up information to this email account- libraryservices@gadsdencountyfl.gov
For a youth card (for students under 18 years of age) send the first name, middle initial and last name, address and birthdate of your child and the name address, email and phone number of the parent or guardian.
For an adult card, send your first name, middle initial, last name a photo of your driver's license or state ID with a Gadsden County Address. New Library Cards are available to Gadsden County residents.

shared_text:
Greensboro Elementary School - Bulldogs
March 30 at 3:58 PM ·

The students may be at home right now, but faculty and staff are out at Greensboro right now making sure kids get their EdPackets for at-home skill practice. We can’t thank our Bulldog team enough for their commitment to our kids. The cafeteria staff have been making and delivering breakfasts and lunches, custodians are doing a deep clean of the campus, and teachers and administrators are doing everything they can think of to help keep our students on track to finish the expectations of this school year. Thanks so much to everyone for everything you’ve contributed to this process.
Oh, and Superintendent Milton stopped by this morning for a wellness check, making sure everyone is healthy and in good spirits. We appreciate your concern, Mr. Milton, and thanks for coming over to see us!
🐶💚💛💚💛💚🐶

post_text:
Gadsden District's BLACK, HINSON, LAWSON & WILSON are all LINKED IN!

The Links, Incorporated of Tallahassee is celebrating its milestone year for the Chapter's Signature Program. The 10th Annual Links Beautillion Program is celebrating and recognizing the accomplishments of 19 high school seniors, four (4) of whom attend Gadsden County Schools. The four (4) students who attend Gadsden County Schools are as follows:
• Jalen Black and Seste Wilson, IV (Crossroad Academy Charter School)
• Phillip Hinson, II and Demetrius Lawson (Gadsden County High School)

These young men have been involved in a 9-week curriculum-based program of extraordinary exposure and opportunities that began on January 12, 2020 at their Green Coat Ceremony. They have participated in Leadership Development, Mentoring, Character Education, etc. Their Program will culminate with a Links Beautillion Formal Presentation and Scholarship Awards on Sunday, March 8, 2020 at 6:00 p.m. at Florida A&M University's Al Lawson Center.

Photos by Anitira Daniels

post_text:
GOOD LUCK to Principal Stokes (James A. Shanks MS) and Assistant Principal Akins (Greensboro ES) as they both compete for the FLDOE Achievement Awards For Outstanding Leadership Programs.

Principal Achievement Award for Outstanding Leadership Program
The Principal Achievement Award for Outstanding Leadership was established in 1988, to recognize exemplary principals for their contributions to their schools and communities. The program honors principals that have spearheaded initiatives to increase student performance, promote safe learning environments and establish partnerships with parents and community members.

Outstanding Assistant Principal Achievement Award Program
The Outstanding Assistant Principal Achievement Award was established in 1997, to recognize exemplary assistant principals for their contributions to their schools and communities. The program honors assistant principals that have utilized teamwork and leadership skills to increase student performance, promote safe learning environments, and establish partnerships with parents and community members.

Gadsden County HS Culinary Art Students serves up a "CHICKEN CACCIATORE SENSATION"

Chef James Bradwell, GCHS students (Niveyonce Carroll, Alexis Kelly, Kenderica Nealy, By'Riona Owens and Aajanae Williams) put their classroom practice skills into action by providing lunch for the Panhandle Area Educational Consortium (PAEC) Board of Directors, hosted by Superintendent Roger P. Milton!

Special thanks to Natalie DuPont-Bradwell, Mary Davis, Joanette Thomas, Anitria Daniels, Jackie Estrada, James Stevens, Kevin Ward and Elijah Israel for assisting with the logistics and coordination of the event. GREAT TEAMWORK!

The PAEC Board of Directors serves as the governing body of PAEC and is comprised of the superintendent of each member school district. Member Districts include Calhoun, FAMU DRS, Franklin, Gadsden, Gulf, Holmes, Jackson, Jefferson, Liberty, Madison, Taylor, Wakulla, Walton and Washington counties.
Panhandle Area Educational Consortium
text:
Gadsden County HS Culinary Art Students serves up a "CHICKEN CACCIATORE SENSATION"

Chef James Bradwell, GCHS students (Niveyonce Carroll, Alexis Kelly, Kenderica Nealy, By'Riona Owens and Aajanae Williams) put their classroom practice skills into action by providing lunch for the Panhandle Area Educational Consortium (PAEC) Board of Directors, hosted by Superintendent Roger P. Milton!

Special thanks to Natalie DuPont-Bradwell, Mary Davis, Joanette Thomas, Anitria Daniels, Jackie Estrada, James Stevens, Kevin Ward and Elijah Israel for assisting with the logistics and coordination of the event. GREAT TEAMWORK!

The PAEC Board of Directors serves as the governing body of PAEC and is comprised of the superintendent of each member school district. Member Districts include Calhoun, FAMU DRS, Franklin, Gadsden, Gulf, Holmes, Jackson, Jefferson, Liberty, Madison, Taylor, Wakulla, Walton and Washington counties.
Panhandle Area Educational Consortium

post_text: A huge congratulations to George W. Munroe Elementary School's Grade 3 students for completing the Health Council of Southeast Florida's OPEN AIRWAYS FOR SCHOOLS course. The American Lung Association course teaches students information about asthma, recognizing and managing asthma symptoms, using medication, avoiding asthma triggers, getting enough exercise and doing well at school. Students are also given materials to take home to their parents. Thank you for making Florida a better place to #BreatheEasy.

CONGRATS to the 2019-20 GADSDEN DISTRICT SPELLING BEE WINNERS!
Charity Monix (Crossroad Academy Charter School) will represent the district at the 2019-2020 Big Bend Regional Spelling Bee, sponsored by Envision Credit Union, on Saturday, March 7, 2020. WFSU will host the event at 1600 Red Barber Plaza, Tallahassee, FL at 9:00 a.m. The Public is welcome to attend. #GoodLuckCharity

District committee: Tammy Farlin, Sarah Knight, Caroline McKinnon, Dr. James Brown, Sharon Thomas and Zola Akins.
